This paper deals with the analysis of Call Detail Records (CDRs) to infer commuting patterns of individuals. This involves the use of machine learning techniques to extract commonalities across locations for different groups of travelers. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with data analysis, privacy concerns, and the use of machine learning techniques.
